abstract: The chip maker, a closely watched indicator of the overall health of the technology industry, reported net income of $1.3 billion, on revenue of $8.7 billion in the second quarter.

lead_paragraph: Intel, a closely watched indicator of the overall health of the technology industry, reported net income of $1.3 billion, or 22 cents a share, on revenue of $8.7 billion in the second quarter, besting analysts’ predictions.
